g\" width=\"566\" height=\"291\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2.jpg 566w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2-297x153.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2-120x62.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2.jpg 566w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2-297x153.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/26130902/K-Edge-aluminum-aero-handlebar-computer-mount-for-new-wahoo-ELEMNT-BOLT-color-2-120x62.jpg 120w\"></a>As a K-Edge mount, we expect the BOLT 2.0 mount to be a precision machined thing of beauty that’s as strong as it is attractive. Made in Boise, ID like the rest of their products, the mount will be machined from 6061-T6 aluminum with an injection molded copolymer interface for the Wahoo mount standard.</p><p>We’re told that these will be released this summer with pricing weight, and features similar to the current BOLT Aero out-front mounts offered by K-Edge. 